Some new/useful linux commands:

Grep:
  Searches files or output for patterns of characters. grep is useful searching through large logs or files for specific text strings.
chmod and chown:
  Used for changing the permissions of files or directories
tail and head:
  these can be used to list the last part or first part of files .

setting static IP on CentOS Linux:
Use the command nmtui to enter gui. Edit the connection. Change IPv4 from automatic to manual. Configure the connection as follows: 

IP Address and Netmask 
10.0.5.3/24
Gateway
10.0.5.2
DNS
10.0.5.5
Search Domain
yourname.local
Hostname
dhcp01-yourname


